rules.original: V → ∅ / #UU(_)U(U(_)U) / unstressed; this "remained as a phonologically conditioned rule in OIr"; "[t]hat’s a little unclear, so let me try and enumerate: in words of more than three syllables, every other vowel (only the even ones) dropped, if it’s unstressed. In some words, syncope didn’t apply because it would create an unwieldy consonant cluster: so PIE *komaktyom → OIr cumachte, not *cumchte"
